ed families in colonial Connecticut."},{"number":2,"category":"politics","header":"First Probate Judge — presided over the Assembly","body":"He became the first Probate Judge of the Guilford district and repeatedly represented Guilford in the Colonial Assembly, serving for a number of sessions as its presiding officer. EH notes he \"became a very prominent man at Guilford.\""},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"His only son died at 21, name extinct","body":"EH notes he \"had but one son who died unmarried, leaving no one to perpetuate his name.\" That son was William, Yale class of 1722, who died at 21."}],"career":[{"role":"Probate Judge","organization":"Guilford District","notes":"First judge of the Guilford probate district; also a town magistrate."},{"role":"Representative","organization":"Connecticut Assembly","notes":"Repeatedly represented Guilford; presiding officer for several sessions."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Hon. James Hooker","title":"Honorable","first_name":"James","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"bio_blurb":"First probate judge of the Guilford district"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"james-hooker-1666"},"I00061":{"id":"I00061","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1672,"month":1,"day":11,"city":"Guilford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1752,"month":10,"day":5,"city":"Guilford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X00065","mother_id":"X00066"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H00031","children_ids":["H00105","H00106","H00107","H00108","H00109"],"marriage_nu